CId\+\_\+\+Export\+Mix&Renders all or part of the session to one or more files. Export Mix (Bounce Mix) can export an entire mix, including sub-\/mixes, to multiple file formats without having to create extra dedicated audio tracks in the session for bus recording. Different options and settings are available depending on the selected File\+Type. The options are organized in sections including Audio, Video, Location, and Dolby Atmos. Here\textquotesingle{}s a breakdown of how the sections are used for each File\+Type\+:


\begin{DoxyItemize}
\item WAV
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has no Video section
\item has a unique field called Delivery\+Format (only shown if Interleaved is selected as the file format and there are multiple mix sources)
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item AIF
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has no Video section
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item MP3
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has no Video section
\item does not allow multiple mix sources
\item does not allow mix sources greater than 0
\item does not allow specifying Bit Depth value (always a 16Bit)
\item Sample Rate is limited to 48k and 44.\+1k
\item Import after Bounce is not available
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item MXF OPAtom
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has no Video section
\item File format is multi-\/mono
\item Bit Depth is only 16Bit and 24Bit
\item Sample Rate is limited to 48k and 44.\+1k
\item Pad to frame boundary is hard-\/coded to ON
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item WAV (Dolby Atmos ADM BWF)
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has no Audio section
\item has no Video section
\item has Dolby Atmos section (unique to this format)
\item has FFOA (bool) default to False
\item if FFOA is true then there\textquotesingle{}s an option to enter Time\+Code value
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item Time\+Code value will match the session frame rate
\item Frame rate will always be 23.\+976 and 30 non-\/drop (if Frame rate is 60 -\/\texorpdfstring{$>$}{>} it will still be 30)
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item has Embed Program-\/level Metadata
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\item None (No file, dry-\/run) -\/ this file \char`\"{}type\char`\"{} is used to do a dry run of an export so plug-\/ins can monitor the export for things like loudness metering, or an export from a renderer plug-\/in. The only fields that are used are\+:
\begin{DoxyEnumerate}
\item mix\+\_\+source\+\_\+list
\item offline\+\_\+bounce
\item start\+\_\+time/end\+\_\+time
\end{DoxyEnumerate}
\end{DoxyItemize}

\begin{DoxyParagraph}{Request body type}
\mbox{\hyperlink{a02272}{Export\+Mix\+Request\+Body}}
\end{DoxyParagraph}

CId\+\_\+\+Get\+Session\+IDs&Provides origin\+Id, instance\+Id and parent\+Id of the current opened session\+: 
\begin{DoxyItemize}
\item origin\+Id is the main ID of the session (or project), and it remains the same in all variations of the session through Save As, Save Copy In, etc.
\item instance\+Id is unique for each session variation. In a new/original session file, the instance\+Id is equal to origin\+Id. When variants are introduced via Save As, Save Copy In, and several others, instance\+Id is set to a new unique ID.
\item parent\+Id is set to the instance\+Id of the source session for sessions based off of a previous session. For new/original sessions, the parent\+Id is set to zeros. That means parent\+Id is equal to origin\+Id for first-\/generation variants, and is different for second and later generation variations.
\end{DoxyItemize}

\begin{DoxyParagraph}{Response body type}
\mbox{\hyperlink{a02604}{Get\+Session\+IDs\+Response\+Body}}
\end{DoxyParagraph}
\begin{DoxyParagraph}{Request body JSON example}

\begin{DoxyCode}{1}
\DoxyCodeLine{\{}
\DoxyCodeLine{    "{}origin\_id"{}: "{}\{00000000-\/2a000000-\/086ed1e0-\/94ef763d\}"{},}
\DoxyCodeLine{    "{}instance\_id"{}: "{}\{00000000-\/2a000000-\/086ed1e0-\/94ef763d\}"{},}
\DoxyCodeLine{    "{}parent\_id"{}: "{}\{00000000-\/00000000-\/00000000-\/00000000\}"{}}
\DoxyCodeLine{\}}

\end{DoxyCode}

\end{DoxyParagraph}

\raisebox{\heightof{T}}[0pt][0pt]{\index{CId\_PollEvents@{CId\_PollEvents}!ptsl@{ptsl}}\index{ptsl@{ptsl}!CId\_PollEvents@{CId\_PollEvents}}}\mbox{\Hypertarget{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aabc3d3419d76198a03985575dff948bce}\label{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aabc3d3419d76198a03985575dff948bce}} 
CId\+\_\+\+Poll\+Events&Streams real-\/time events from Pro Tools to the client. This RPC runs indefinitely without a typical end condition. It does not accept input arguments, relying on other methods for event system configuration. Each In\+Progress struct with the event is considered a new event.

Only one active connection is allowed per PTSL session. If a new call is made within the same session, the polling is transferred to the new connection, terminating the previous one if active.

The method runs immediately, bypassing the command queue.

The method is not affected by the timeout mechanism.

The method does not suppress Pro Tools UI alerts.

See the \mbox{\hyperlink{a04105}{article}} for more details on how to use the event system.

\DoxyCodeLine{    \}}
\DoxyCodeLine{\}}

CId\+\_\+\+Get\+Track\+Control\+Info&Return information about controls on a track. \begin{DoxyNote}{Note}
Defined but not yet implemented
\end{DoxyNote}
Provide a way to query for information about one or more track controls.

Use track\+\_\+id to select the track. If it is empty all tracks are queried.~\newline
 Or multiple tracks can be listed and queried.

Use \mbox{\hyperlink{a02948}{Track\+Control\+Id}} to specify a filter for which controls to query. Any values provided~\newline
 in the control\+\_\+id parameter can be used to filter which controls to query. Empty fields~\newline
 match everything.

In response the value range and number of steps for the control are returned. For~\newline
 each control the control\+\_\+id is also defined. For pan controls, this will give you~\newline
 the pan space that a pan control is operating in.

CId\+\_\+\+Set\+Track\+Control\+Breakpoints&Sets a value on a target track control. Use \mbox{\hyperlink{a02948}{Track\+Control\+Id}} to specify whether you are targetting track volume, panning, LFE level, or an insert plug-\/in. Volume and pan can be either on the main output or a send.

In a \mbox{\hyperlink{a02956}{Track\+Control\+Breakpoint}} the {\ttfamily time} to place the value at is paired with the {\ttfamily value} itself. A single value can be passed in to set the default.~\newline
 Or multiple values can specify a series of automation breakpoints. A value at time zero must always be included.~\newline
 Any existing values for the control are replaced by those from this call. Values can be either floating point or integers, depending on the needs of the control. Use \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aa02fb9c48c42d2995ae880343393b60e4}{CId\+\_\+\+Get\+Track\+Control\+Info}} to get the allowed range of values.

\raisebox{\heightof{T}}[0pt][0pt]{\index{CId\_InstallMenuHandler@{CId\_InstallMenuHandler}!ptsl@{ptsl}}\index{ptsl@{ptsl}!CId\_InstallMenuHandler@{CId\_InstallMenuHandler}}}\mbox{\Hypertarget{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aa59a8b2486d07a5bdedfaeb18dd62e5df}\label{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aa59a8b2486d07a5bdedfaeb18dd62e5df}} 
CId\+\_\+\+Install\+Menu\+Handler&This command can be used to install a custom menu item into Pro Tools menus. The client provides the menu label and where in the app to put the menu item.

Once a menu item is installed, the client must be running \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aabc3d3419d76198a03985575dff948bce}{CId\+\_\+\+Poll\+Events}} to recieve notifications when the item is selected by the user. CId\+\_\+\+Poll\+Events will notify the client that a \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_a4cf8d4a4d56e9f795518b6541ddeb5bfa2f5c92785d6d203d478771ff2b76d91a}{EId\+\_\+\+Menu\+Item\+Selected}} event has happened. The response will include the {\ttfamily menu\+\_\+item\+\_\+id} that is returned by this function to differentiate among multiple installed menu handlers. But it is opaque and no other assumptions should be made about its value.

The command auto-\/subscribes to \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_a4cf8d4a4d56e9f795518b6541ddeb5bfa2f5c92785d6d203d478771ff2b76d91a}{EId\+\_\+\+Menu\+Item\+Selected}} events, as if \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aa3123650ddf7f82ade0c8def87b1f7f40}{CId\+\_\+\+Subscribe\+To\+Events}} were called.

Use \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_aaf8d2069e2c6bbecf4aa8f9819028e8aaf0888e59c80a4010c661b42e2cd2ca69}{CId\+\_\+\+Uninstall\+Menu\+Handler}} to clean up.

\begin{DoxyParagraph}{Request body type}
\mbox{\hyperlink{a02996}{Install\+Menu\+Handler\+Request\+Body}}
\end{DoxyParagraph}
\begin{DoxyParagraph}{Request body JSON example}

\begin{DoxyCode}{1}
\DoxyCodeLine{\{}
\DoxyCodeLine{  "{}menu\_info"{}: \{}
\DoxyCodeLine{    "{}menu\_area"{}: "{}MArea\_Import"{},}
\DoxyCodeLine{    "{}menu\_label"{}: [}
\DoxyCodeLine{      \{"{}locale"{}: "{}en"{}, "{}string"{}: "{}Menu label in English"{}\},}
\DoxyCodeLine{      \{"{}locale"{}: "{}zh-\/cn"{}, "{}string"{}: "{}Menu label in Simplified Chinese"{}\}}
\DoxyCodeLine{    ]}
\DoxyCodeLine{  \}}
\DoxyCodeLine{\}}

\end{DoxyCode}

\end{DoxyParagraph}

\DoxyCodeLine{\}}

\end{DoxyCode}

{\footnotesize\ttfamily enum \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_ad3f5e2afc55060cfcef65710cb99afbe}{Pan\+Space}}}



The pan space in which a pan control is defined. 

{\ttfamily Sphere} refers to spherical coordinates. {\ttfamily Cart} refers to cartesian coordinates. 2-\/layer means the upper hemisphere only. 3-\/layer includes the lower hemisphere, below the floor.

Compatible controls for each pan space are defined in \mbox{\hyperlink{a00494_ac0685ec9d387e632efc9a12c1cbe4da2}{Pan\+Control\+Parameter}}.
